Multi-Container Docker Application

This project shows a Docker-based multi-service application made up of several containers working together. The application includes the following components:

Frontend web service built with Node.js
Backend API service
Worker service
Redis for caching
PostgreSQL as the database
RabbitMQ for message queuing
Prerequisites

Before running the project, make sure the following are installed on your system:

Docker
Docker Compose
Steps to Run the Project
Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/nbajagain/urbaneats-docker-lab.git
Move into the project directory:
cd urbaneats-docker-lab
Build and start all containers:
docker compose up --build
Service URLs

After the application starts, you can access the services using these links:

Main Web App: http://localhost
API Health Check: http://localhost/api/health
RabbitMQ Dashboard: http://localhost:15672
Shutting Down the Application

To stop and remove the running containers, use:

docker compose down
